B. Averaging of Data
The use of averaging of features value enables the reduction of data volumes in a control fashion to improve effective data processing.
Functions Used in the Code :
df.groupby("Category").mean()
* Groups the dataset by a specified column (e.g., "Category") and calculates the mean for numerical features.
* Useful for aggregating data based on categorical values.
Code:	
import pandas as pd

data = {
    "Category": ["A","A","A","B","B","C","C"],
    "Value1": [10,20,30,40,50,60,70],
    "Value2": [20,30,40,50,60,70,80],
    "Value3": [30,40,50,60,70,80,90]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
df.to_csv("IP_DATA_CORE.csv", index=False)
print("Sample CSV created!")

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("IP_DATA_CORE.csv")

# Data reduction
if "Category" in df.columns:
    df_reduced = df.groupby("Category").mean()
else:
    df_reduced = df.mean(numeric_only=True).to_frame().T

# Save file
df_reduced.to_csv("data_reduced.csv", index=True)

print("Data reduction complete!")

